	That's probably because 'rmdir' checks for its argument.
$ uname
FreeBSD
$ cd /tmp
$ mkdir TT
$ cd TT
$ rmdir .
rmdir: .: Invalid argument
$ rmdir /tmp/TT
$ ls
ls: .: No such file or directory
$ 
